{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ESPn7u9qiH7dZSwqXzZLNA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the findings:\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's a complete analysis of how workflow graphs are rendered in the web UI:\n\n## Summary of Workflow Graph Rendering in Cloche\n\n### 1. Domain Types (Workflow Structure)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\nThe core domain types are:\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire\n    Collects  []Collect\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", or \"workflow\"\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string\n    Result    string\n    To        string\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n    Mode       CollectMode  // \"all\" or \"any\"\n    Conditions []WireCondition\n    To         string\n}\n\ntype WireCondition struct {\n    Step   string\n    Result string\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Web UI Files\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\nThe web UI consists of:\n\n- **Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1983 lines)\n- **Templates:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `layout.html` - Base HTML layout\n  - `projects.html` - Projects overview page\n  - `project_detail.html` - Individual project page with graph rendering\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Individual run page with execution details\n- **Styles:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 3. Graph Rendering Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 172-434)\n\nThe workflow graph is rendered entirely in **client-side JavaScript** using **SVG**. The implementation includes:\n\n#### Graph Layout Algorithm\n- **Topological sort** using Kahn's algorithm (lines 204-226)\n- **Layer assignment** using longest-path heuristics - Sugiyama-style layering (lines 228-244)\n- **Barycenter ordering** for edge crossing minimization (lines 252-282)\n- **Position calculation** (lines 284-305):\n  - `nodeW = 180` (node width)\n  - `nodeH = 48` (node height)\n  - `layerGap = 120` (horizontal gap between layers)\n  - `nodeGap = 28` (vertical gap between nodes)\n  - `nonsuccOffset = 35` (vertical offset for non-success wires)\n\n#### SVG Elements\n- **Nodes:** Rectangles with text labels and emoji icons\n  - Regular steps: Script (📜), Agent (🤖), Workflow (🔄)\n  - Terminal nodes: \"done\" (green, rounded), \"abort\" (red, rounded)\n- **Edges:** Cubic Bezier curves connecting nodes\n  - Success wires: normal style\n  - Non-success wires: darker/failure style with offset curves\n- **Edge Labels:** Step results (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", etc.)\n- **Merge Patterns:** For multiple wires to same terminal, uses:\n  - Individual curves from sources\n  - Vertical collector line with dots\n  - Single line to terminal\n\n#### CSS Classes for Graph Styling\n- `.dag-svg` - SVG container with horizontal scrolling\n- `.dag-node-rect` - Node rectangle styling\n- `.dag-node-text` - Node text styling\n- `.dag-edge` - Edge line styling\n- `.dag-edge-label` - Edge label styling\n- `.dag-edge-nonsuccess` - Failed result styling\n- `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - Terminal node colors\n- `.dag-merge-line` / `.dag-merge-dot` - Merge visualization\n\n### 4. Web Handler API Endpoints\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Key endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` (lines 1457-1574)\n\nReturns JSON array with structure:\n```go\ntype apiWorkflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    File      string\n    Location  string  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     []apiStepDef\n    Wires     []apiWire\n    EntryStep string\n}\n\ntype apiStepDef struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    string\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype apiWire struct {\n    From   string\n    Result string\n    To     string\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Workflow Loading and Rendering Flow\n\n1. **Page Load:** `project_detail.html` calls `loadWorkflows()` (line 103)\n2. **API Call:** Fetches `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n3. **Data Processing:**\n   - Filters workflows by location (container vs host)\n   - Renders location tabs if both exist\n   - Renders workflow tabs for multiple workflows\n4. **Graph Rendering:** `showWorkflow(wf)` function (lines 172-434)\n   - Builds adjacency maps\n   - Performs topological sort\n   - Assigns layers via longest-path algorithm\n   - Applies barycenter heuristic to minimize crossings\n   - Calculates node positions\n   - Generates SVG markup\n   - Inserts into DOM\n\n### 6. Interactive Features\n\n- **Node Click:** Opens drawer with step details (config, type, results)\n- **Step Drawer:** Side panel showing:\n  - Step type\n  - Results list\n  - Step configuration\n  - Step content/prompt (if available)\n- **Keyboard:** Escape key closes drawer\n- **Responsive:** Adapts to different screen sizes\n\n### 7. File Paths Summary\n\n**Web UI Root:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - HTTP handlers and API endpoints\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Graph rendering logic\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - All styling including DAG CSS\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run execution types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n\n### 8. Graph Visualization Constants\n\nFrom `project_detail.html` lines 285-289:\n- Node Width: 180px\n- Node Height: 48px\n- Layer Horizontal Gap: 120px\n- Node Vertical Gap: 28px\n- Non-success Offset: 35px\n- Padding Left/Top: 30px each\n\nThe graph uses a **Sugiyama-style hierarchical layout** with **Bezier curves** for edges, supporting **merge patterns** for multiple wires to the same target, and **visual differentiation** for success vs. failure paths."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae375162a7de22fbe (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64890\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 52523</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5f57d13-6940-497b-9967-e6dfa7c6b1ef","uuid":"61ede7cc-5110-4eda-b147-b061c1b39e61","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand how workflow graphs are rendered in the web UI. I need to find:\n\n1. The web UI files (HTML templates, CSS, JavaScript) that render workflow graphs\n2. How workflow steps/nodes are currently laid out\n3. How wiring/links between nodes are rendered\n4. Any existing graph layout logic\n5. The domain types for workflows, steps, results, and wiring\n\nSearch thoroughly in:\n- internal/adapters/ (especially anything web/http related)\n- cmd/ directories\n- Any .html, .js, .css, .tmpl files\n- internal/domain/ for workflow types\n\nBe very thorough - check all naming conventions like \"web\", \"ui\", \"http\", \"template\", \"graph\", \"workflow\", \"render\", \"layout\".","agentId":"ae375162a7de22fbe","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the findings:\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's a complete analysis of how workflow graphs are rendered in the web UI:\n\n## Summary of Workflow Graph Rendering in Cloche\n\n### 1. Domain Types (Workflow Structure)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\nThe core domain types are:\n\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire\n    Collects  []Collect\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", or \"workflow\"\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string\n    Result    string\n    To        string\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n    Mode       CollectMode  // \"all\" or \"any\"\n    Conditions []WireCondition\n    To         string\n}\n\ntype WireCondition struct {\n    Step   string\n    Result string\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Web UI Files\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\nThe web UI consists of:\n\n- **Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1983 lines)\n- **Templates:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `layout.html` - Base HTML layout\n  - `projects.html` - Projects overview page\n  - `project_detail.html` - Individual project page with graph rendering\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Individual run page with execution details\n- **Styles:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 3. Graph Rendering Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 172-434)\n\nThe workflow graph is rendered entirely in **client-side JavaScript** using **SVG**. The implementation includes:\n\n#### Graph Layout Algorithm\n- **Topological sort** using Kahn's algorithm (lines 204-226)\n- **Layer assignment** using longest-path heuristics - Sugiyama-style layering (lines 228-244)\n- **Barycenter ordering** for edge crossing minimization (lines 252-282)\n- **Position calculation** (lines 284-305):\n  - `nodeW = 180` (node width)\n  - `nodeH = 48` (node height)\n  - `layerGap = 120` (horizontal gap between layers)\n  - `nodeGap = 28` (vertical gap between nodes)\n  - `nonsuccOffset = 35` (vertical offset for non-success wires)\n\n#### SVG Elements\n- **Nodes:** Rectangles with text labels and emoji icons\n  - Regular steps: Script (📜), Agent (🤖), Workflow (🔄)\n  - Terminal nodes: \"done\" (green, rounded), \"abort\" (red, rounded)\n- **Edges:** Cubic Bezier curves connecting nodes\n  - Success wires: normal style\n  - Non-success wires: darker/failure style with offset curves\n- **Edge Labels:** Step results (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", etc.)\n- **Merge Patterns:** For multiple wires to same terminal, uses:\n  - Individual curves from sources\n  - Vertical collector line with dots\n  - Single line to terminal\n\n#### CSS Classes for Graph Styling\n- `.dag-svg` - SVG container with horizontal scrolling\n- `.dag-node-rect` - Node rectangle styling\n- `.dag-node-text` - Node text styling\n- `.dag-edge` - Edge line styling\n- `.dag-edge-label` - Edge label styling\n- `.dag-edge-nonsuccess` - Failed result styling\n- `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - Terminal node colors\n- `.dag-merge-line` / `.dag-merge-dot` - Merge visualization\n\n### 4. Web Handler API Endpoints\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**Key endpoint:** `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` (lines 1457-1574)\n\nReturns JSON array with structure:\n```go\ntype apiWorkflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    File      string\n    Location  string  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     []apiStepDef\n    Wires     []apiWire\n    EntryStep string\n}\n\ntype apiStepDef struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    string\n    Results []string\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype apiWire struct {\n    From   string\n    Result string\n    To     string\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Workflow Loading and Rendering Flow\n\n1. **Page Load:** `project_detail.html` calls `loadWorkflows()` (line 103)\n2. **API Call:** Fetches `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n3. **Data Processing:**\n   - Filters workflows by location (container vs host)\n   - Renders location tabs if both exist\n   - Renders workflow tabs for multiple workflows\n4. **Graph Rendering:** `showWorkflow(wf)` function (lines 172-434)\n   - Builds adjacency maps\n   - Performs topological sort\n   - Assigns layers via longest-path algorithm\n   - Applies barycenter heuristic to minimize crossings\n   - Calculates node positions\n   - Generates SVG markup\n   - Inserts into DOM\n\n### 6. Interactive Features\n\n- **Node Click:** Opens drawer with step details (config, type, results)\n- **Step Drawer:** Side panel showing:\n  - Step type\n  - Results list\n  - Step configuration\n  - Step content/prompt (if available)\n- **Keyboard:** Escape key closes drawer\n- **Responsive:** Adapts to different screen sizes\n\n### 7. File Paths Summary\n\n**Web UI Root:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - HTTP handlers and API endpoints\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Graph rendering logic\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - All styling including DAG CSS\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow domain types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run execution types\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n\n### 8. Graph Visualization Constants\n\nFrom `project_detail.html` lines 285-289:\n- Node Width: 180px\n- Node Height: 48px\n- Layer Horizontal Gap: 120px\n- Node Vertical Gap: 28px\n- Non-success Offset: 35px\n- Padding Left/Top: 30px each\n\nThe graph uses a **Sugiyama-style hierarchical layout** with **Bezier curves** for edges, supporting **merge patterns** for multiple wires to the same target, and **visual differentiation** for success vs. failure paths."}],"totalDurationMs":52523,"totalTokens":64890,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_cre