{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VGfiaeTJJ2VoXGbkmTS7sa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`** — Rewrote the workflow graph edge rendering in `showWorkflow()`:\n\n1. **Color mapping**: Each wire result type gets a distinct color — green for success/ok/done/pass, red for failed/fail/error, then blue/yellow/magenta/cyan/orange for other result types\n2. **Per-color arrowhead markers**: Dynamic SVG `<marker>` defs created for each color used\n3. **Offset link nodes for failure paths**: Non-success wires to terminals (done/abort) are routed through a separate lane below the main flow:\n   - Vertical drop from each source node's bottom to a horizontal lane\n   - Link node circles at each junction point\n   - Horizontal lane connecting all junctions\n   - Bezier curve from lane end up to the terminal node\n4. **Success paths draw directly**: Success wires to terminals use simple colored Bezier curves as before\n\n**`internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** — Added `.dag-link-node` class for junction circle styling\n\n**`internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`** — Updated `TestProjectDetail_RendersLayoutEngine` assertions to match the new rendering approach (checking for `nonSuccTermGroups`, `wireColor`, `laneY`, `markerRef` instead of the removed merge pattern elements)\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":707,"cache_read_input_tokens":76412,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":707},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5f57d13-6940-497b-9967-e6dfa7c6b1ef","uuid":"63a30fc8-7087-4407-a768-3cc8193a308c"}
